1
00:00:05,172 --> 00:00:06,632
Pete: I told you that
one of the side effects

2
00:00:06,716 --> 00:00:09,009
of the meds that you're on
is hallucinations.

3
00:00:11,595 --> 00:00:13,055
We're still trying
to piece together

4
00:00:13,139 --> 00:00:14,515
the things
that you don't remember.

5
00:00:15,349 --> 00:00:19,270
I keep hoping that we will reach
a point where we can grieve.

6
00:00:19,353 --> 00:00:20,646
Theresa's not dead.

7
00:00:20,730 --> 00:00:22,189
You don't have to
come by anymore.

8
00:00:22,273 --> 00:00:23,774
It's not good for you
to be here.

9
00:00:23,816 --> 00:00:26,444
I am one of the biggest boosters
of this team.

10
00:00:26,527 --> 00:00:28,028
Please.
Don't come by.

11
00:00:28,738 --> 00:00:30,156
It's over, John.

12
00:00:30,239 --> 00:00:32,658
It is not over
until I saw that it is over!

13
00:00:32,742 --> 00:00:34,034
John: You put me back
on a bad path,

14
00:00:34,118 --> 00:00:36,162
you made me think
about bad things.

15
00:00:36,245 --> 00:00:37,580
And now here we are.

16
00:00:37,663 --> 00:00:39,832
I know something,
you know something.

17
00:00:39,915 --> 00:00:42,168
We found a necklace
on the remains.

18
00:00:42,209 --> 00:00:44,962
-It's our daughter's.
-Shh.

19
00:00:45,045 --> 00:00:46,130
We're closed.

20
00:00:47,631 --> 00:00:48,716
I hoped
I'd just catch you.

21
00:00:51,051 --> 00:00:56,807
♪

22
00:00:56,891 --> 00:00:58,893
That necklace belonged
to Theresa Barlow.

23
00:00:59,852 --> 00:01:02,313
The missing girl,
the one whose mother

24
00:01:02,396 --> 00:01:03,439
-has made it her life's work...
-I know. I know.

25
00:01:03,522 --> 00:01:04,940
I know who she is.

26
00:01:05,024 --> 00:01:06,066
...to prove that
you're as guilty as Parker.

27
00:01:07,485 --> 00:01:10,279
-You still sure?
-Of what?

28
00:01:10,362 --> 00:01:11,530
You never saw her.

29
00:01:12,156 --> 00:01:13,783
You never crossed paths
with her?

30
00:01:14,700 --> 00:01:16,869
The only thing that happened
in those woods, was--

31
00:01:18,871 --> 00:01:20,748
was giving birth to Freya.
That's all I know.

32
00:01:20,831 --> 00:01:22,291
I don't know anything
about a body.

33
00:01:23,375 --> 00:01:24,794
Maybe you blocked it out.

34
00:01:26,045 --> 00:01:27,963
Do you think that
I could forget seeing that?

35
00:01:28,047 --> 00:01:29,089
Yeah, I do.

36
00:01:29,882 --> 00:01:31,050
I think this is it.

37
00:01:32,301 --> 00:01:36,222
I think this is the event that
triggered your memory blackouts.

38
00:01:36,305 --> 00:01:37,181
That's it.

39
00:01:38,140 --> 00:01:41,310
Yeah, well, that's--
that's great for you, Pete.

40
00:01:41,393 --> 00:01:43,479
I'm happy. I'm happy that
you have some closure.

41
00:01:43,562 --> 00:01:44,939
A body was found
in Minnesota...

42
00:01:45,064 --> 00:01:46,106
No, remains.
You said remains.

43
00:01:46,190 --> 00:01:47,024
Pete: From the time you
and him were arrested.

44
00:01:47,107 --> 00:01:48,317
It could be an animal.
It could be anything.

45
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:51,070
The skull was bashed in.

46
00:01:51,153 --> 00:01:52,571
Most likely by a hammer.

47
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,865
Emma, it's him.

48
00:01:54,949 --> 00:01:57,159
This was Parker, and I think
you were there,

49
00:01:57,243 --> 00:01:59,119
and I think you saw all of this,
and I think

50
00:01:59,203 --> 00:02:02,122
that you have blocked out
everything ever since.

51
00:02:02,206 --> 00:02:03,624
So take a look.

52
00:02:06,377 --> 00:02:07,837
I don't remember.

53
00:02:09,755 --> 00:02:11,090
Well, you'd better try.

54
00:02:11,799 --> 00:02:13,843
Because pretty soon,
the FBI is gonna ask me

55
00:02:13,926 --> 00:02:15,177
what I think you know.

56
00:02:17,388 --> 00:02:22,142
Again, please take a look.

57
00:02:26,438 --> 00:02:31,193
Sometimes,
I get these... flashes.

58
00:02:36,240 --> 00:02:37,658
But I don't know
what they are, Pete.

59
00:02:37,741 --> 00:02:41,453
I don't know
if they're nightmares or...

60
00:02:41,495 --> 00:02:46,166
[breathing heavily]

61
00:02:46,250 --> 00:02:47,459
...or memories.

62
00:02:48,544 --> 00:02:51,964
♪ Every time I close my eyes ♪

63
00:02:52,047 --> 00:02:56,719
♪ I can touch the colors
Around me ♪

64
00:02:56,802 --> 00:03:00,639
♪ Suddenly, I realize ♪

65
00:03:00,723 --> 00:03:01,932
♪ Everything ♪

66
00:03:02,016 --> 00:03:03,142
You're not keeping
any of it?

67
00:03:06,145 --> 00:03:08,272
Throwing photos away.

68
00:03:08,355 --> 00:03:10,316
I should've done this
a long time ago.

69
00:03:11,734 --> 00:03:15,446
I made frittata...
it's in the fridge.

70
00:03:15,529 --> 00:03:16,989
When?

71
00:03:17,072 --> 00:03:19,617
Last night.
Didn't sleep.

72
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:22,745
I made chocolate chip cookies,
too... your favorite.

73
00:03:23,454 --> 00:03:25,247
Yeah, when I was eight.

74
00:03:30,044 --> 00:03:31,503
We're gonna
get through this.

75
00:03:33,964 --> 00:03:35,341
I'm fine, Mom.

76
00:03:38,010 --> 00:03:39,303
Okay.

77
00:03:45,768 --> 00:03:52,733
♪

78
00:03:57,780 --> 00:03:58,822
[Sniffles]

79
00:04:00,366 --> 00:04:01,617
-Ow!
-Oh, shit!

80
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:03,035
I'm so sorry.

81
00:04:04,286 --> 00:04:05,537
Are you okay?

82
00:04:07,081 --> 00:04:14,046
♪

83
00:04:19,593 --> 00:04:20,844
Band-Aids in the back.

84
00:04:20,928 --> 00:04:23,514
[ Rustling ]

85
00:04:28,268 --> 00:04:30,896
You're the girl from Seattle,
aren't you?

86
00:04:30,980 --> 00:04:32,147
[ Growls ]

87
00:04:34,441 --> 00:04:36,318
You seem troubled.

88
00:04:36,402 --> 00:04:43,367
♪

89
00:04:47,663 --> 00:04:52,584
When you're ready
to figure it out, come see me.

90
00:04:52,668 --> 00:04:59,633
♪

91
00:05:02,970 --> 00:05:04,972
Thank you so much.
Take care.

92
00:05:05,055 --> 00:05:06,432
All right.

93
00:05:08,017 --> 00:05:09,393
[ Door opens, bell jingles ]

94
00:05:13,439 --> 00:05:14,732
[ Door closes, bell jingles ]

95
00:05:15,941 --> 00:05:22,906
♪

96
00:05:28,454 --> 00:05:35,419
♪

97
00:05:37,629 --> 00:05:44,595
♪

98
00:05:49,683 --> 00:05:52,019
-Hey.
-Hey.

99
00:05:55,647 --> 00:05:56,732
You okay?

100
00:05:58,859 --> 00:06:01,695
No.
I don't think I am.

101
00:06:03,072 --> 00:06:06,033
So, uh, Caterina says you're
trouble and you believe her?

102
00:06:06,116 --> 00:06:09,203
No, not that I'm trouble,
that I'm troubled.

103
00:06:09,286 --> 00:06:10,621
It's a big difference.

104
00:06:11,914 --> 00:06:13,791
Is there something
you're not telling me?

105
00:06:13,874 --> 00:06:15,709
Isn't that
the craziest question

106
00:06:15,793 --> 00:06:17,878
when you really
think about it?

107
00:06:21,548 --> 00:06:23,217
There's so many things...

108
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:27,805
that all of us aren't
telling each other...

109
00:06:27,888 --> 00:06:29,556
all of the time.

110
00:06:29,640 --> 00:06:30,766
What is it?

111
00:06:31,433 --> 00:06:36,313
This just isn't about
Caterina Keep, right?

112
00:06:36,396 --> 00:06:37,981
Give me credit for that.

113
00:06:38,899 --> 00:06:40,692
[ Sighs ]

114
00:06:40,776 --> 00:06:42,236
What do you see...

115
00:06:43,862 --> 00:06:45,531
when you look at me?

116
00:06:46,615 --> 00:06:49,368
You're a cop, you see a lot of
people in a lot of situations.

117
00:06:49,451 --> 00:06:52,412
You must be pretty good
at reading them, so...

118
00:06:52,496 --> 00:06:59,461
♪

119
00:07:05,008 --> 00:07:09,096
♪

120
00:07:09,179 --> 00:07:11,598
I see that little freckle.

121
00:07:11,682 --> 00:07:17,062
♪

122
00:07:17,146 --> 00:07:20,023
I see you got
a little dimple.

123
00:07:20,107 --> 00:07:25,112
♪

124
00:07:25,195 --> 00:07:26,989
That's not what I mean.

125
00:07:29,491 --> 00:07:31,535
I mean, like, really,
what do you see?

126
00:07:32,786 --> 00:07:35,247
Like deeper
than the freckle?

127
00:07:35,330 --> 00:07:37,332
Yeah, like deeper
than the freckle.

128
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:39,710
What do you see?

129
00:07:42,921 --> 00:07:44,840
Someone I wanna be with.

130
00:07:44,923 --> 00:07:50,179
♪

131
00:07:54,975 --> 00:07:58,645
-♪ Everything ♪
-[Hammer pounding]

132
00:07:58,729 --> 00:08:01,398
♪ Shines much brighter ♪

133
00:08:01,481 --> 00:08:06,820
♪ I want to fly
Into this beautiful life ♪

134
00:08:06,904 --> 00:08:09,656
♪ I think it'd nice with you ♪

135
00:08:09,740 --> 00:08:15,078
♪ I want to fly
Into this beautiful life ♪

136
00:08:15,162 --> 00:08:21,043
♪ I think it'd nice with you ♪

137
00:08:21,126 --> 00:08:25,547
♪ With you ♪

138
00:08:25,631 --> 00:08:29,968
♪ With you ♪

139
00:08:30,052 --> 00:08:33,847
♪ With you ♪

140
00:08:33,931 --> 00:08:37,893
♪ Set the night on fire
If we want to ♪

141
00:08:39,811 --> 00:08:43,482
[Both panting]

142
00:08:43,565 --> 00:08:50,530
♪

143
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:57,871
♪

144
00:08:58,914 --> 00:09:00,332
Where have you gone?

145
00:09:02,292 --> 00:09:09,258
♪

146
00:09:11,677 --> 00:09:18,642
♪

147
00:09:20,769 --> 00:09:23,981
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

148
00:09:31,113 --> 00:09:38,078
♪

149
00:09:40,539 --> 00:09:44,418
♪ Fingertips, northern lights ♪

150
00:09:44,501 --> 00:09:48,839
♪ Tracing colors
Right through the sky ♪

151
00:09:48,922 --> 00:09:52,592
-♪ Underneath a lullaby ♪
-[ Sighs ]

152
00:09:52,676 --> 00:09:56,305
-She loved this song.
-Yep.

153
00:09:56,388 --> 00:09:58,181
I just want to keep
hearing it, you know?

154
00:09:58,265 --> 00:10:00,475
Yep.
I got that.

155
00:10:00,559 --> 00:10:06,565
♪ And my heart sings
In a world so incredible ♪

156
00:10:06,648 --> 00:10:10,861
It's a bench, for her.

157
00:10:10,944 --> 00:10:12,821
♪ Shines much brighter ♪

158
00:10:12,904 --> 00:10:17,284
♪ I want to fly
Into this beautiful life ♪

159
00:10:17,367 --> 00:10:20,787
It's something I've been
thinking about for

160
00:10:20,871 --> 00:10:22,789
a long time.

161
00:10:22,873 --> 00:10:24,875
Looks good.

162
00:10:24,958 --> 00:10:28,170
Listen, I know there's, uh,
gonna be a big memorial,

163
00:10:28,253 --> 00:10:29,963
from the trust...
I just...

164
00:10:32,799 --> 00:10:34,676
I don't know if I really want
the bench inside some church

165
00:10:34,760 --> 00:10:36,928
that she was never
even in before.

166
00:10:37,929 --> 00:10:40,849
I was thinking maybe we could
do something, the three of us.

167
00:10:40,932 --> 00:10:43,060
Say some prayers,
lay some flowers.

168
00:10:43,143 --> 00:10:45,687
I was thinking we could do it,
uh, out at Calaveras Lake.

169
00:10:46,897 --> 00:10:48,523
Yeah, she loved it
out there.

170
00:10:48,607 --> 00:10:51,109
♪ Hanging out with the stars ♪

171
00:10:51,193 --> 00:10:53,695
We were thinking
maybe late tomorrow.

172
00:10:53,779 --> 00:10:56,156
♪ I very well thank you ♪

173
00:10:56,239 --> 00:10:58,617
Oh, uh, I don't know, Saul.

174
00:10:58,700 --> 00:11:01,036
I have that conference.

175
00:11:01,870 --> 00:11:03,538
♪ Set the night on fire ♪

176
00:11:03,622 --> 00:11:05,957
Doesn't have to be tomorrow.
We-- We want you there.

177
00:11:06,041 --> 00:11:08,418
♪ Hanging out with the stars
And the big moon ♪

178
00:11:08,502 --> 00:11:11,213
[ Sighs ]
Listen, it's a great spot.

179
00:11:11,296 --> 00:11:13,965
You're absolutely right
on where you want to put it.

180
00:11:14,049 --> 00:11:15,884
You don't have to build it
around me.

181
00:11:15,967 --> 00:11:21,723
♪ I think it'd be
Nice with you ♪

182
00:11:21,807 --> 00:11:23,683
♪ With you ♪

183
00:11:26,436 --> 00:11:29,106
[ Birds crying ]

184
00:11:38,573 --> 00:11:40,033
[ Popping ]

185
00:11:53,380 --> 00:11:54,589
[ Trunk slams ]

186
00:12:18,947 --> 00:12:20,365
Everything okay
over here?

187
00:12:20,449 --> 00:12:22,075
I'm fine. I'm cool.

188
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:23,034
Thank you.
I know what I'm doing.

189
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:23,994
Good luck.

190
00:12:26,580 --> 00:12:29,666
[ Car approaches ]

191
00:12:33,545 --> 00:12:35,589
I'm fine!
I'm fine!

192
00:12:35,672 --> 00:12:37,632
Keep going.
Thank you.

193
00:12:38,550 --> 00:12:39,801
Ha.

194
00:12:42,262 --> 00:12:44,181
You kiss your mother
with that finger?

195
00:12:46,475 --> 00:12:49,102
[ Birds singing ]

196
00:13:01,114 --> 00:13:02,616
Oh, hi.

197
00:13:04,409 --> 00:13:05,744
Car trouble?

198
00:13:05,827 --> 00:13:07,621
Unfortunately so.

199
00:13:10,415 --> 00:13:11,791
Huh.

200
00:13:11,875 --> 00:13:13,210
I just read that one.

201
00:13:13,293 --> 00:13:15,378
Oh.
You like it?

202
00:13:15,462 --> 00:13:18,882
It's, uh, enough to make a guy
like me stop writing.

203
00:13:18,965 --> 00:13:21,676
Oh.
I never met a writer before.

204
00:13:21,760 --> 00:13:23,512
I've never met
a cop before.

205
00:13:23,595 --> 00:13:25,430
-John.
-Tom.

206
00:13:26,556 --> 00:13:29,601
So, uh, you got problems
under your hood.

207
00:13:29,684 --> 00:13:31,811
Well, I assume you're talking
about the car.

208
00:13:31,895 --> 00:13:33,313
That's how little
I know about...

209
00:13:33,396 --> 00:13:36,566
Yeah.
I know even less.

210
00:13:36,650 --> 00:13:38,985
I'll have someone come out
to you.

211
00:13:39,069 --> 00:13:41,446
-We'll get you moving.
-Oh.

212
00:13:41,530 --> 00:13:43,073
Hey, would it
be presumptuous

213
00:13:43,156 --> 00:13:46,743
if I caught a ride
with you into town?

214
00:13:46,826 --> 00:13:49,746
I'm kind of on the way home,
so...

215
00:13:49,829 --> 00:13:52,582
I was just hoping to get
to the hotel.

216
00:13:52,666 --> 00:13:54,292
Gonna meet my girl there.

217
00:13:57,504 --> 00:13:58,880
-Thank you so much.
-Sure.

218
00:13:58,964 --> 00:14:00,590
Thank you.

219
00:14:00,674 --> 00:14:02,175
Okay.

220
00:14:02,259 --> 00:14:03,468
Down.

221
00:14:09,432 --> 00:14:10,308
[ Car door closes ]

222
00:14:10,433 --> 00:14:11,977
Uh, would you mind putting
the lights on for me?

223
00:14:12,060 --> 00:14:14,896
Please? So I could feel
like I'm in a movie?

224
00:14:15,981 --> 00:14:18,149
[ Siren chirps ]

225
00:14:18,233 --> 00:14:21,278
So, um, what brings
you out here?

226
00:14:21,361 --> 00:14:23,113
Love.

227
00:14:23,196 --> 00:14:25,448
Well, love will make you
do crazy things.

228
00:14:25,532 --> 00:14:26,950
Tell me about it.

229
00:14:27,033 --> 00:14:29,786
Are we a couple of, uh,
live-action,

230
00:14:29,869 --> 00:14:32,247
role playing romantics, Tom?

231
00:14:32,330 --> 00:14:34,749
I guess we are.

232
00:14:34,833 --> 00:14:36,585
Then, uh,
what's the bar in town

233
00:14:36,668 --> 00:14:38,670
that's really gonna
blow my girl away?

234
00:14:38,753 --> 00:14:41,339
Thursday nights at The Fly Trap
are pretty fun.

235
00:14:41,423 --> 00:14:44,342
I mean, it's nicer
than it sounds.

236
00:14:44,426 --> 00:14:46,803
[ Laughs ]
Yeah, that doesn't seem hard.

237
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:49,889
Now you can buy me a drink
for insulting my bar.

238
00:14:51,141 --> 00:14:53,310
Hey, you're on.

239
00:14:53,393 --> 00:14:55,270
Let's do it.
I owe you.

240
00:15:02,819 --> 00:15:05,739
♪ Touch the colors around me ♪

241
00:15:05,822 --> 00:15:09,367
♪ Suddenly, I realize ♪

242
00:15:09,451 --> 00:15:10,702
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

243
00:15:10,785 --> 00:15:15,373
♪ Everything I thought
Was impossible is here ♪

244
00:15:15,457 --> 00:15:19,336
♪ And my heart sings ♪

245
00:15:19,419 --> 00:15:21,212
♪ In a world so incredible ♪

246
00:15:21,296 --> 00:15:23,632
[ Buzzing continues ]

247
00:15:31,014 --> 00:15:32,182
John: Mary?

248
00:15:34,392 --> 00:15:37,854
She's gone, John.

249
00:15:40,273 --> 00:15:41,900
My daughter.

250
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:49,032
So now it's time for you
to just get on with your life.

251
00:15:49,115 --> 00:15:52,160
That's what I'm doing.
That's what we're all doing.

252
00:15:52,243 --> 00:15:53,536
It's over.

253
00:15:53,620 --> 00:15:55,288
I didn't find her.

254
00:15:56,373 --> 00:15:59,250
No, Mary, no.

255
00:15:59,334 --> 00:16:00,543
This is not you talking.

256
00:16:00,627 --> 00:16:02,962
This is not my Mary.

257
00:16:03,046 --> 00:16:06,091
I'm not your Mary.

258
00:16:06,174 --> 00:16:09,052
This is grief.

259
00:16:09,135 --> 00:16:11,054
You're not thinking clearly.

260
00:16:11,137 --> 00:16:14,182
No, I'm--
I'm finally thinking clearly.

261
00:16:14,265 --> 00:16:15,600
Okay, John?

262
00:16:15,684 --> 00:16:17,185
-Goodbye.
- Unh-unh.

263
00:16:17,268 --> 00:16:18,603
I'm gonna call you tomorrow,
okay?

264
00:16:18,687 --> 00:16:20,730
I'm not-- I'm not gonna
abandon you.

265
00:16:20,814 --> 00:16:22,315
Not when you need me most.

